{\par \b Syntax:}\par pivot(Mtrx(A),Intg(nl),Intg(nc))\par
{\par \b Description:}\par Returns the matrix from A creating zeros in the column nc, by the method of Gauss-Jordan with the element A[nl,nc] as pivot.\par
{\par \b Example:}\par pivot([[1,2],[3,4],[5,6]],0,1) returns [[1,2],[0,-2],[0,-4]]\par }